# src/app/ - Page Router & App Structure

## Purpose
Next.js App Router pages. Each file/folder = route.

## Routing Convention

```
src/app/
├── page.tsx                # /
├── layout.tsx              # Root layout (wraps all pages)
├── calculators/
│   ├── page.tsx            # /calculators (all calculators listing)
│   ├── [slug]/
│   │   └── page.tsx        # /calculators/[slug] (dynamic calculator pages)
├── categories/
│   └── [category]/
│       └── page.tsx        # /categories/[category] (category listing)
├── about/
│   └── page.tsx            # /about
├── contact/
│   └── page.tsx            # /contact
├── privacy/
│   └── page.tsx            # /privacy
├── terms/
│   └── page.tsx            # /terms
├── sitemap.ts              # /sitemap.xml (auto-generated)
└── robots.ts               # /robots.txt (auto-generated)
```

## Page Component Pattern

Every page must have:

1. **Metadata** (SEO)
```tsx
import { Metadata } from 'next';

export const metadata: Metadata = {
  title: 'Mortgage Calculator | ToolNest',
  description: 'Free mortgage calculator. Estimate your monthly payment...',
  openGraph: {
    title: 'Mortgage Calculator | ToolNest',
    description: 'Free mortgage calculator...',
    url: 'https://toolnest.com/calculators/mortgage-calculator',
    images: [{ url: '/og-image.png' }],
  },
};
```

2. **Component** (functional)
```tsx
export default function Page() {
  return (
    // Page content
  );
}
```

3. **No inline styles** (use Tailwind)

4. **Reuse layouts & sections** (don't duplicate code)

## Dynamic Pages: Calculators

File: `calculators/[slug]/page.tsx`

```tsx
import { CalculatorLayout } from '@/components/calculators/CalculatorLayout';
import { getToolBySlug } from '@/lib/data/tools';
import { getContent } from '@/lib/data/content';

export async function generateMetadata({ params }): Promise<Metadata> {
  const tool = getToolBySlug(params.slug);
  return {
    title: tool.title,
    description: tool.metaDescription,
  };
}

export async function generateStaticParams() {
  const tools = getAllTools();
  return tools.map((tool) => ({ slug: tool.slug }));
}

export default function CalculatorPage({ params }) {
  const tool = getToolBySlug(params.slug);
  const content = getContent(params.slug);

  return <CalculatorLayout tool={tool} content={content} />;
}
```

**Why:** Static generation at build time. Zero runtime overhead.

## Category Pages

File: `categories/[category]/page.tsx`

Similar pattern to calculators, but shows grid of tools + category intro.

## Sitemap & Robots

- `sitemap.ts` - auto-generates from tools.ts (includes all calculators, categories, static pages)
- `robots.ts` - simple allow all (no disallows)

Both exported as static files at build time.

## Static Pages

Each static page (about, privacy, contact) follows same pattern:
- Metadata at top
- Functional component
- Reuse sections (HeroSection, FAQSection, etc.)

## Layout Hierarchy

```
layout.tsx (root)
├── page.tsx (homepage)
├── calculators/
│   ├── layout.tsx (optional, if calc-specific layout needed)
│   ├── page.tsx (all calculators)
│   └── [slug]/page.tsx (individual calculator)
├── about/page.tsx
└── ...
```

Root layout provides:
- Header (sticky nav)
- Footer
- Theme provider (dark mode)
- Global styles

---

## Performance Notes

- Static generation preferred (no dynamic data)
- Use `generateStaticParams()` to pre-generate dynamic routes
- ISR (incremental static regeneration) if content changes frequently

---

## Common Mistakes

❌ **Importing heavy libraries in page.tsx**
- Use dynamic import if needed: `const Component = dynamic(() => import('...'))`

❌ **Hardcoding content in page.tsx**
- Load from `lib/data/content/{slug}.json`

❌ **No metadata export**
- Always export Metadata object for SEO

✅ **Data from tools.ts**
- All tool metadata flows from single source

✅ **Layout reuse**
- Use CalculatorLayout for all calculators (not separate page per tool)

---

## Testing Page

Before committing:
1. Render page locally: `npm run dev`
2. Check metadata in browser <head> (view source)
3. Mobile responsive (DevTools 320px-1440px)
4. Lighthouse audit (Performance ≥90)
5. No console errors/warnings
